<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41021e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41021e">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41021e"> 21(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> affinity</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Marriage Act, 1835, (following the canonical law) prohibited certain marriages on the ground of the kindred or <mark>affinity</mark> of the parties; and such marriages are void for all purposes. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 18</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
